  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies arguments for selecting a font face, including the collection index, color palette, and variable font axis positions.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a mutable struct that bundles arguments for selecting or customizing a font face. It supports specifying a TrueType Collection (TTC) font index, a color palette, per-entry palette color overrides, and variable font axis positions.

Pass an `SKFontArguments` value to <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)> to derive a customized typeface from an existing one.

## Examples

```csharp
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex = 0,
    PaletteIndex = 1,
    VariationDesignPosition = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[]
    {
        new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Create('w','g','h','t'), Value = 700f }
    }
};

using var typeface = originalTypeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
